3. Figma File Semantics


Layer naming convention (ARIA APG aligned)

role / identifier [aria-notes]
Examples:

button / submit [aria-label="Submit form"]
input / email [type=email, required, aria-describedby=email-error]
dialog / confirm-delete [aria-modal=true, aria-labelledby=dialog-title]
radio-group / payment [role=radiogroup]
radio / credit-card [aria-checked=false]
accordion-item / faq-1
  heading / faq-1-title [aria-level=3]
    button / faq-1-trigger [aria-expanded=false, aria-controls=faq-1-panel]
  panel / faq-1-panel [role=region, hidden]


Auto-layout = semantic structure
Auto-layout direction must reflect reading order and DOM order
Vertical AL = block-level elements (form fields, accordion items, list items)
Horizontal AL = inline elements (button group, tabs, breadcrumb)
Nested AL depth should mirror HTML nesting depth
NEVER use absolute positioning for semantically ordered content


Component variants = ARIA states
| Figma variant property | ARIA equivalent |
|------------------------|-----------------|
| State=default | (no attribute) |
| State=hover | (visual only, no ARIA change) |
| State=focus | :focus-visible |
| State=active | aria-pressed=true (toggles) |
| State=disabled | aria-disabled=true |
| State=error | aria-invalid=true |
| State=loading | aria-busy=true |
| Checked=true | aria-checked=true |
| Expanded=true | aria-expanded=true |
| Selected=true | aria-selected=true |



Semantic root detection
When a user selects a single star in a star-rating group, analyze the
SEMANTIC ROOT, not the selected node:


function getSemanticRoot(node) {
  let cursor = node
  while (cursor.parent && cursor.parent.type !== "PAGE") {
    const parent = cursor.parent
    if (!("children" in parent)) break
    const siblings = parent.children
    const allSameType = siblings.length >= 2 &&
      siblings.every(s => s.type === cursor.type)
    const semanticParent = ["group","radio","star","rating","check",
      "tab","toggle","segment","toolbar","menu","list"]


