4. Accessibility — Core Principles


WCAG 2.2 AA — the non-negotiables
Every audit must check these. No exceptions.



| Criterion | Requirement | Severity if failed |
|-----------|-------------|-------------------|
| 1.4.3 | Text contrast ≥ 4.5:1 (normal), 3:1 (large) | BLOCKER |
| 1.4.11 | UI component contrast ≥ 3:1 (borders, icons, focus rings) | BLOCKER |
| 1.4.1 | No info conveyed by color alone | BLOCKER |
| 2.4.7 | Focus visible (focus ring exists and is visible) | BLOCKER |
| 2.5.3 | Label in name (button text matches accessible name) | BLOCKER |
| 2.5.8 | Touch target ≥ 24×24px (44×44 recommended) | BLOCKER |
| 3.3.2 | Labels or instructions for inputs | BLOCKER |
| 4.1.2 | Name, role, value for all UI components | BLOCKER |
| 1.3.1 | Info and relationships conveyed in structure | HIGH |
| 2.4.6 | Headings and labels descriptive | HIGH |



ARIA APG — structural rules per component


Button

role=button or native <button>
Icon-only: aria-label required (no exceptions)
Link-style button: use role=link, not role=button
Toggle: aria-pressed=true/false
aria-label must match or contain visible label text (2.5.3)


Radio group

role=radiogroup on container with aria-labelledby pointing to group label
Each option: role=radio + aria-checked
Star rating: each star needs aria-label="N stars" (not just a visual)
Keyboard: arrow keys move between options (document in annotation)


Checkbox

Tri-state: aria-checked="mixed" for indeterminate
Group: role=group, not role=radiogroup
Each checkbox: aria-labelledby pointing to its label


Accordion

Structure: heading[aria-level] > button[aria-expanded, aria-controls]
NOT button > heading (this is the most common mistake)
Panel: role=region, aria-labelledby=trigger-id
aria-level must match document hierarchy (ask the designer)


Dialog

role=dialog, aria-modal=true
aria-labelledby pointing to visible heading inside dialog
Destructive action: role=alertdialog
Must have close mechanism (button with aria-label="Close")
Focus annotation: opens → first focusable element; closes → trigger


Combobox

role=combobox, aria-expanded, aria-haspopup=listbox
Listbox: role=listbox, each option role=option + aria-selected
Chevron icon: aria-hidden=true always
If no type-to-search: annotate as select pattern instead


Text input

label element is required. Placeholder is NOT a label substitute.
error message: role=alert or aria-live=polite, connected via aria-describedby
required: aria-required=true + visual indicator (not asterisk alone)


Checkbox in multi-select context

Container: role=group with aria-labelledby
Select-all: if present, aria-controls listing all checkbox IDs


What you CANNOT detect programmatically (be honest about this)
Whether an error state is "color only" (requires human visual review)
Reading order when using absolute positioning + z-index
Whether focus ring contrast is sufficient without computing actual colors
Whether a decorative image is truly decorative
Motion/animation impact (prefers-reduced-motion)


When a check requires human judgment, report it as:

{ severity: "MANUAL", message: "Verify this manually: ...", wcag: "1.4.1" }


