5. Performance Rules


Never do on large files

// ✗ walks every node in the document
figma.currentPage.findAll(...)

// ✓ scope to the relevant container
frame.findAllWithCriteria({ types: ["INSTANCE", "TEXT"] })


Batch scan — always chunk

async function batchScan(nodes) {
  const results = []
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    results.push(scanNode(nodes[i]))
    if (i % 20 === 0) {
      figma.notify(`Scanning... ${i}/${nodes.length}`, { timeout: 500 })
      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 0))  // yield
    }
  }
  return results


Limit traversal depth
Default max depth: 5 levels
For spatial text search: scan only same page, not all pages
For sibling detection: limit to 20 siblings max


AI calls — minimize cost
Rule engine handles HIGH confidence cases (target: ≥ 85% of selections)
Only MED/LOW go to AI
Pass only text data to AI — no screenshots unless absolutely necessary
Use gpt-4o-mini as default, not gpt-4o
Cache AI results in pluginData — don't re-call for same node if unchanged


