6. Code Quality Rules


Never hardcode node IDs

// ✗ will break on any other file
figma.getNodeById("1833:121")

// ✓ always resolve dynamically
const root = getSemanticRoot(figma.currentPage.selection[0])


Resolve semantic slugs to real IDs before mutating

// AI returns { nodeId: "rating-star" } — not a real Figma ID
// Always run resolveSuggestions() before applyFixes()
const resolved = resolveSuggestions(suggestions, rootNode)


Guard every node access

const node = figma.getNodeById(id)
if (!node) { /* handle gracefully, don't throw */ return }
if (!("name" in node)) { /* not a SceneNode */ return }


ASK before mutating
NEVER rename layers, set plugin data, or create nodes without user confirmation
For HIGH confidence: show suggestions, wait for "Apply Fixes" click
For MED confidence: show ASK question first, then suggestions
Batch scan: queue all ASK questions, don't open multiple dialogs


postMessage contract — typed messages only

// Always use typed message objects
type PluginMessage =
  | { type: "ANALYZE_SELECTION" }
  | { type: "APPLY_FIXES"; suggestions: Suggestion[]; rootNodeId: string }
  | { type: "SAVE_API_KEY"; key: string }
  | { type: "ASK_ANSWER"; questionId: string; answer: string; rootNodeId: string }


