7. Dev Mode Integration


When in Dev Mode, the plugin behaves differently
No "Apply Fixes" (read-only context for developers)
Show only: role, aria attributes, issues, WCAG references
Display copy-pasteable ARIA attribute list (not HTML)


What developers need (not HTML snippets)

// ✓ technology-agnostic ARIA data
{
  "role": "button",
  "aria-label": "Submit form",
  "aria-disabled": false,
  "states": {
    "focus": { "aria-describedby": "tooltip-id" },
    "loading": { "aria-busy": true, "aria-label": "Submitting..." }
  },
  "wcag": ["1.4.3", "2.5.5", "2.4.7"],


Shared plugin data — always write for dev access

node.setSharedPluginData("a11y", "role", "button")
node.setSharedPluginData("a11y", "ariaLabel", "Submit form")
node.setSharedPluginData("a11y", "issues", JSON.stringify(issues))


