8. What to Always Ask the Designer


Before applying any fix, ask:

"What heading level (h1–h6) should this accordion use in context?"
"Is this button navigating somewhere (link) or triggering an action (button)?"
"Is this dialog confirming a destructive action? (determines alertdialog vs dialog)"
"Does this accordion allow multiple items open simultaneously?"
"Is this chip removable, selectable, or display-only?"
"What is the error message text for this input field?"
"Does this icon button have a tooltip that serves as its accessible name?"


Never assume. Always confirm ambiguity before writing plugin data.

