## 9. Self-Healing — Never Fail When You Can Fix

The plugin must NEVER show a blocker and stop. Every detected issue
must first attempt a self-repair before asking the designer.

### Resolution priority order (apply in this sequence):
1. Fix automatically with AI-generated content (max 1000 chars I/O)
2. Fix automatically with a safe generic fallback
3. Ask the designer to choose between options
4. Only escalate to MANUAL if none of the above is possible

### Per-issue self-repair map:

| Issue code          | Auto-fix strategy |
|---------------------|-------------------|
| NO_GROUP_LABEL      | AI-generate label from option texts → create text layer above component |
| NO_INPUT_LABEL      | AI-generate label from input name/placeholder → create text layer above |
| NO_ARIA_LABEL       | AI-generate from node name + context → write to pluginData only |
| MISSING_ERROR_STATE | Create error variant copy with red border + "Error" text layer |
| MISSING_FOCUS_STATE | Duplicate default state + add 2px #4DA3FF outline stroke |
| MISSING_DISABLED    | Duplicate default state + set opacity to 40% |
| NO_CLOSE_BUTTON     | Add icon button "✕" to dialog header corner |
| NO_HEADING          | AI-generate heading text from dialog/accordion content |
| MISSING_PLACEHOLDER | Generic: "Enter [field name] here" |
| TOUCH_TARGET_SMALL  | Wrap node in auto-layout frame, set min width/height to 44px |

### AI text generation rules:
- Input cap: 800 chars (option labels + component name + context)
- Output cap: 60 chars (UI labels are short)
- Model: gpt-4o-mini only (cost)
- Prompt template:
  "You write short ARIA labels for UI components.
   Component: [type]. Options/content: [text list].
   Write a [3-6 word] label. Return label text only."
- Always fallback to generic if AI fails or no API key

### After auto-fix:
- Re-run the audit on the fixed node
- If issue resolved → remove from issue list, show ✅ "Auto-fixed"
- If still failing → escalate to designer with the specific question

### What counts as "truly needs designer":
- Contrast ratio fail (requires color change decision)
- Wrong heading level (requires information architecture decision)
- Icon button with no text context (AI cannot guess intent)
- Destructive action confirmation (role=alertdialog decision)

